# AGENTS.local.md (example)

This is an **example template** for a personal `AGENTS.local.md` file. To use it, copy this file to `AGENTS.local.md` at the repository root and edit it to suit your needs:

```bash
cp AGENTS.local.md-example AGENTS.local.md
```

`AGENTS.local.md` is git-ignored (see `.gitignore`), so your local notes stay out of source control. Do not commit it.

## Ground rules

* This file is **additive only**. It must not override, weaken, or contradict the rules in `AGENTS.md`. If a conflict arises, `AGENTS.md` wins.
* Keep entries scoped to your local environment, in-flight work, or personal preferences—nothing that should ship to the team belongs here.
* Delete sections you do not use; agents will read whatever is present.

---

